### Step 9: Git Commit Processing (New File)

**New file**: `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/kolkata-v1/app/src/server/webhook/github-commit-processor.ts`

This follows the same structure as `document-ingestion.ts`: create source record, run extraction, persist, write embeddings.

```typescript
export async function processGitCommit(input: {
  surreal: Surreal;
  extractionModel: any;
  embeddingModel: any;
  embeddingDimension: number;
  extractionStoreThreshold: number;
  extractionModelId: string;
  workspaceRecord: RecordId<"workspace", string>;
  commit: {
    sha: string;
    message: string;
    authoredAt: string;
    authorName: string;
    authorEmail: string;
    url: string;
    repository: string;
  };
  workspaceName?: string;
  projectNames?: string[];
  now: Date;
}): Promise<ProcessGitCommitResult> {
  // 1. Check for existing git_commit by SHA (idempotency via UNIQUE index)
  // 2. Resolve author person record (findWorkspacePersonByName or match by email)
  // 3. Create git_commit record with workspace field
  // 4. Create embedding for commit message
  // 5. Run extractStructuredGraph() with:
  //    - conversationHistory: [] (no conversation context)
  //    - graphContext: load workspace graph context
  //    - sourceText: commit.message
  //    - onboarding: false
  // 6. Run persistExtractionOutput() with:
  //    - sourceRecord: commitRecord as SourceRecord
  //    - sourceKind: "git_commit"
  //    - sourceCommitRecord: commitRecord
  //    - no sourceMessageRecord, no sourceChunkRecord
  // 7. Auto-link high-confidence decision evidence:
  //    - For each extracted decision entity with confidence >= 0.85:
  //      Create implemented_by edge (decision -> git_commit)
  //    - For confidence 0.6-0.85: create observation (info severity)
  //      "Commit <sha> may implement decision <name> - please confirm"
  // 8. Write embedding to git_commit record
  // 9. Return results
}
```

**Auto-linking logic** (the confidence-based linking from requirements):

```typescript
async function autoLinkDecisionEvidence(input: {
  surreal: Surreal;
  workspaceRecord: RecordId<"workspace", string>;
  commitRecord: RecordId<"git_commit", string>;
  commitSha: string;
  extractedEntities: ExtractedEntity[];
  autoLinkThreshold: number;  // 0.85
  now: Date;
}): Promise<void> {
  for (const entity of input.extractedEntities) {
    if (entity.kind !== "decision") continue;

    const decisionRecord = new RecordId("decision", entity.id);

    if (entity.confidence >= input.autoLinkThreshold) {
      // High confidence: auto-link via implemented_by
      await input.surreal.relate(
        decisionRecord,
        new RecordId("implemented_by", randomUUID()),
        input.commitRecord,
        {
          commit_sha: input.commitSha,
          linked_at: input.now,
        },
      ).output("after");
    } else {
      // Low confidence: create observation for user review
      await createObservation({
        surreal: input.surreal,
        workspaceRecord: input.workspaceRecord,
        text: `Commit ${input.commitSha.slice(0, 8)} may implement decision "${entity.text}" (confidence: ${(entity.confidence * 100).toFixed(0)}%). Please confirm.`,
        severity: "info",
        sourceAgent: "git_webhook",
        now: input.now,
        relatedRecord: decisionRecord,
      });
    }
  }
}
```

**Idempotency**: The `git_commit_sha` UNIQUE index prevents duplicate creation. The handler should query for existing commit by SHA first and skip if already processed.

